he passed away, he was
one of our participants.

00:06:25.940 --> 00:06:29.440
Clara Giannini, as a
long-time board member.

00:06:29.440 --> 00:06:34.440
And actually, Clara
Giannini and Janet Pomeroy

00:06:36.560 --> 00:06:40.180
back in the 1960s, and Eunice Shriver,

00:06:40.180 --> 00:06:41.980
we have photos of them all together.

00:06:41.980 --> 00:06:46.020
That's what makes this
award so interesting to me,

00:06:46.020 --> 00:06:50.970
because between these women who,

00:06:50.970 --> 00:06:55.040
you know you think back
to the 1950s, early 1960s,

00:06:55.040 --> 00:06:57.570
wasn't easy for women to own any business,

00:06:57.570 --> 00:07:01.800
start any business, let
alone programs like this.

00:07:01.800 --> 00:07:04.360
But when you look at the
history of our country,

00:07:04.360 --> 00:07:09.360
that's really who drove the
models that we have today.

00:07:09.410 --> 00:07:13.010
And it's amazing.

00:07:13.010 --> 00:07:15.290
We have a dance and yoga studio.

00:07:15.290 --> 00:07:18.410
So one of the things that makes our

00:07:18.410 --> 00:07:20.670
day activity program a little unique,

00:07:20.670 --> 00:07:22.832
and in fact just two Sundays ago,

00:07:22.832 --> 00:07:26.230
myself and another staff
member were in Hawaii

00:07:26.230 --> 00:07:29.560
at a Pac Rim disability conference

00:07:29.560 --> 00:07:31.750
sponsored by the University of Hawaii,

00:07:31.750 --> 00:07:33.660
and we were talking about our day program

00:07:33.660 --> 00:07:36.860
because it is an educational program.

00:07:36.860 --> 00:07:41.000
We have over 45 classes, we run
it like a community college.

00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:43.800
And in fact two of the classes are run by

00:07:43.800 --> 00:07:47.240
community college professors, and students

00:07:47.240 --> 00:07:49.140
from the outside can come and take

00:07:49.140 --> 00:07:52.130
their art or drama at the Pomeroy Center

00:07:52.130 --> 00:07:53.743
along with our participants.

